<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1998]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1778,1804]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet derives from the Latin “ 
<taxonomicName box="[860,937,1779,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquila">aquila</taxonomicName>
” [= dark-colored]; referring to infuscation on the anterior part of the wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1998]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1856,1882]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[686,933,1856,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[686,811,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">V. fasciata</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by tergite 
<number box="[241,257,1895,1921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
with white recumbent scales anteriorly and tergites 
<number box="[929,980,1895,1921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" value="1.5">1, 5</number>
, and 
<number box="[1049,1065,1895,1921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" value="6.0">6</number>
with white recumbent scales posteriorly. In 
<taxonomicName box="[339,471,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[339,471,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">V. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tergites 
<number box="[591,638,1933,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
have yellowish recumbent scales antero-laterally, tergite 
<number box="[1370,1386,1933,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
has yellowish recumbent scales anteriorly, and tergites 
<number box="[750,793,1972,1998]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
have yellowish recumbent scales posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
